other_tests.findings: The appendix is fluid-filled measuring up to 1 cm with wall edema. There is periappendiceal fluid. Findings are compatible with acute appendicitis. No free air in the abdomen. The remainder of the large bowel is unremarkable.
There is a small amount of free fluid around the tip of the appendix. The urinary bladder, distal ureters, seminal vesicles, prostate, sigmoid colon, and rectum are unremarkable.
Localized tenderness in RLQ, non-distended abdomen. Guarding and rebound tenderness present. No edema in extremities; distal pulses palpable +2.
